==English==

===Etymology===
Attested since the mid 16th century, of uncertain origin. Suggestions include connection with Irish Gaelic {{term|cauch||cup|lang=ga}} (whence Scots {{term|quaich|lang=sco}}, {{term|queff|lang=sco}}). The noun is derived from the verb, since the later 16th century.

